SIMPLE: flex_time
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: flex time
<hw>flex"
time`</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[short for
<ets>flexible time</ets>.]</ety> <def>A system of scheduling working
hours in places of employment, which allows employees to arrive at and
leave work at times of their own choice, providing that they work the
required number of hours and usually requiring that they be present
during certain hours, called <part>core time</part>.</def> <note>Certain
workers prefer to arrive early and leave early, and others prefer to
arrive late and leave late. <ex>Flex time</ex> is a way to accommodate
such preferences, presumably improving employee morale, and also helps
reduce traffic congestion during commmuting times.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flexuose</ent>⟦br⟧
